>> McAfee: Yes.

00:14:57.062 --> 00:14:59.198 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: And McAfee
subsequently gets purchased

00:14:59.198 --> 00:15:00.599 align:middle line:90%
by Intel, what happened there?

00:15:00.599 --> 00:15:04.069 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: They are purchased by
Intel for eight billion I think.

00:15:04.069 --> 00:15:04.837 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: How much?

00:15:04.837 --> 00:15:06.105 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Eight billion.

00:15:06.105 --> 00:15:08.274 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Eight billion
from a little tiny company--

00:15:08.274 --> 00:15:10.576 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: A little tiny
company for eight million.

00:15:10.576 --> 00:15:14.113 align:middle line:84%
Again, it's a fast-growing
field.

00:15:14.113 --> 00:15:15.314 align:middle line:90%
And software security

00:15:15.314 --> 00:15:18.617 align:middle line:84%
and information security
is really the [inaudible]

00:15:18.617 --> 00:15:22.755 align:middle line:84%
of everything without the
security, we lose everything.

00:15:22.755 --> 00:15:26.058 align:middle line:84%
I mean, think about it, if there
were no software protections,

00:15:26.058 --> 00:15:29.361 align:middle line:84%
firewalls, antivirus software,
you couldn't run your computer

00:15:29.361 --> 00:15:31.530 align:middle line:84%
for more than five
minutes before it crashed.

00:15:31.530 --> 00:15:32.665 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Gees.

00:15:32.665 --> 00:15:34.700 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: So it's an
extremely important part

00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:37.169 align:middle line:84%
of this entire information
process.

00:15:37.169 --> 00:15:41.040 align:middle line:84%
But in any case, I
started Tribal Voice

00:15:41.040 --> 00:15:42.474 align:middle line:84%
which was an instant
messaging company

00:15:42.474 --> 00:15:45.377 align:middle line:84%
and then the same thing
happened only much quicker, OK?

00:15:45.377 --> 00:15:48.581 align:middle line:90%
So I sold out after 18 months

00:15:48.581 --> 00:15:50.449 align:middle line:84%
for I think 17 million
and went up--

00:15:50.449 --> 00:15:51.517 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Good for you.

00:15:51.517 --> 00:15:52.651 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: -- and
formed another company.

00:15:52.651 --> 00:15:55.221 align:middle line:84%
And I'm afraid that's
the only thing I'm good

00:15:55.221 --> 00:15:56.422 align:middle line:90%
for is starting things--

00:15:56.422 --> 00:15:58.157 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Starting,
selling, and getting out.

00:15:58.157 --> 00:15:59.692 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Start out and selling
and just getting out because--

00:15:59.692 --> 00:16:01.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: What do you
think of the Facebook boys?

00:16:01.760 --> 00:16:02.895 align:middle line:90%
Zuckerberg

00:16:02.895 --> 00:16:03.963 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Well I think
Facebook is spectacular.

00:16:03.963 --> 00:16:07.132 align:middle line:84%
I mean, as a social--
as a social tool,

00:16:07.132 --> 00:16:09.735 align:middle line:84%
I personally don't spend
much time on Facebook,

00:16:09.735 --> 00:16:11.704 align:middle line:84%
I prefer to do face
time with real people.

00:16:11.704 --> 00:16:13.105 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Yeah.

00:16:13.105 --> 00:16:14.240 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: I think this is one
of the props in the world today.

00:16:14.240 --> 00:16:17.109 align:middle line:84%
By the way our technology
has isolated us

00:16:17.109 --> 00:16:19.078 align:middle line:90%
from the human community.

00:16:19.078 --> 00:16:20.412 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: So true.

00:16:20.412 --> 00:16:23.983 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: We go into places
and people are just looking

00:16:23.983 --> 00:16:27.119 align:middle line:84%
at their smartphones and
they're texting and--

00:16:27.119 --> 00:16:29.989 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: I saw a couple of
four people go to dinner, right,

00:16:29.989 --> 00:16:32.057 align:middle line:84%
not one of them John
looked at each other.

00:16:32.057 --> 00:16:33.259 align:middle line:84%
That's right, they're
just on their phones.

00:16:33.259 --> 00:16:34.526 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: And they're texting

00:16:34.526 --> 00:16:35.261 align:middle line:84%
and they could be texting
each other for all I know.

00:16:35.261 --> 00:16:36.095 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Yeah.

00:16:36.095 --> 00:16:37.396 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: I mean, you know--

00:16:37.396 --> 00:16:38.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: They don't know
how to talk with each other.

00:16:38.230 --> 00:16:39.598 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Or they use it for--

00:16:39.598 --> 00:16:41.934 align:middle line:84%
I don't know, it could be the
man texting the other man's

00:16:41.934 --> 00:16:44.169 align:middle line:84%
wife, you know, well,
meet you after--

00:16:44.169 --> 00:16:48.140 align:middle line:84%
you don't have a clue
but it's not comfortable,

00:16:48.140 --> 00:16:52.044 align:middle line:84%
it's not a comfortable image
in my mind of the direction

00:16:52.044 --> 00:16:53.479 align:middle line:90%
that humanity is taking.

00:16:53.479 --> 00:16:56.649 align:middle line:84%
Given what we're doing
with that technology.

00:16:56.649 --> 00:17:00.286 align:middle line:84%
Now, we could use
technology totally differently

00:17:00.286 --> 00:17:05.157 align:middle line:84%
if we had more wisdom
and more courage.

00:17:05.157 --> 00:17:09.261 align:middle line:84%
But I fear that if it
continues in this way,

00:17:09.261 --> 00:17:12.898 align:middle line:84%
we're going to have remote
sects, remote everything.

00:17:12.898 --> 00:17:13.732 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Remote everything.

00:17:13.732 --> 00:17:14.800 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Remote everything.

00:17:14.800 --> 00:17:16.034 align:middle line:84%
And so-- and we're
going to think we live

00:17:16.034 --> 00:17:21.407 align:middle line:84%
in an absolute heaven of
reality but it will collapse

00:17:21.407 --> 00:17:22.640 align:middle line:90%
around us at some point.

00:17:22.640 --> 00:17:24.543 align:middle line:84%
Reality will intrude
no matter what we do.

00:17:24.543 --> 00:17:26.412 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Or somebody's,
dotcom companies--

00:17:26.412 --> 00:17:29.581 align:middle line:84%
fab companies like
Twitter and, you know,

00:17:29.581 --> 00:17:32.384 align:middle line:84%
we saw what Facebook
did to Myspace.

00:17:32.384 --> 00:17:33.786 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Right.

00:17:33.786 --> 00:17:35.521 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Will there always be
a new evolution-- I mean now--

00:17:35.521 --> 00:17:36.755 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Of course.

00:17:36.755 --> 00:17:37.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: -- it's, you know,
Snapchat and Instagram--

00:17:37.890 --> 00:17:38.691 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Of course.

00:17:38.691 --> 00:17:39.825 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: They keep coming.

00:17:39.825 --> 00:17:40.960 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: There will
always be an evolution

00:17:40.960 --> 00:17:44.430 align:middle line:84%
because there is no end
to technological growth.

00:17:44.430 --> 00:17:47.232 align:middle line:84%
There is no end to
human imagination.

00:17:47.232 --> 00:17:48.634 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Right.

00:17:48.634 --> 00:17:51.937 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: And the imagination--
the image of Twitter for example

00:17:51.937 --> 00:17:56.275 align:middle line:84%
which occurred to the founders,
wow, what a great concept.

00:17:56.275 --> 00:17:58.043 align:middle line:84%
I believe there will
be a greater concept

00:17:58.043 --> 00:17:59.011 align:middle line:90%
and a greater concept.

00:17:59.011 --> 00:17:59.778 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: How do
they monetize that?

00:17:59.778 --> 00:18:00.746 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: pardon?

00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:01.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: How do
they monetize that?

00:18:01.680 --> 00:18:02.881 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: There
is the question.

00:18:02.881 --> 00:18:04.350 align:middle line:84%
They-- actually Twitter
went public two days ago,

00:18:04.350 --> 00:18:05.351 align:middle line:90%
three days ago.

00:18:05.351 --> 00:18:06.685 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: A couple
of days ago, yeah.

00:18:06.685 --> 00:18:08.887 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: It came out of
the price of 26 dollars

00:18:08.887 --> 00:18:11.423 align:middle line:90%
and opened instantly at 45.

00:18:11.423 --> 00:18:13.025 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: With minimal
earnings, right?

00:18:13.025 --> 00:18:13.726 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: No earnings.

00:18:13.726 --> 00:18:14.426 align:middle line:90%
To my knowledge--

00:18:14.426 --> 00:18:15.728 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: No earnings.

00:18:15.728 --> 00:18:17.363 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: -- I don't think
they're making any money.

00:18:17.363 --> 00:18:21.266 align:middle line:84%
However, anything that the
world has to use, believe me,

00:18:21.266 --> 00:18:22.968 align:middle line:84%
you will find a way
to make money.

00:18:22.968 --> 00:18:24.603 align:middle line:84%
And this is why people
are investing.

00:18:24.603 --> 00:18:25.537 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Yeah.

00:18:25.537 --> 00:18:27.306 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: So that
was astonishing.

00:18:27.306 --> 00:18:29.641 align:middle line:90%
So for-- in 30 seconds,

00:18:29.641 --> 00:18:32.578 align:middle line:84%
people got 90 percent
on their investment.

00:18:32.578 --> 00:18:33.245 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Just crazy.

00:18:33.245 --> 00:18:34.013 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Isn't it?

00:18:34.013 --> 00:18:34.847 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: It's just crazy.

00:18:34.847 --> 00:18:36.849 align:middle line:90%
So John McAfee then sales out,

00:18:36.849 --> 00:18:40.119 align:middle line:84%
you've got your funds,
you go to Belize.

00:18:40.119 --> 00:18:40.986 align:middle line:90%
Why did you go there?

00:18:40.986 --> 00:18:42.655 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: A couple of reasons.

00:18:42.655 --> 00:18:44.790 align:middle line:84%
It's the most beautiful
country in the world physically.

00:18:44.790 --> 00:18:46.325 align:middle line:90%
I mean-- or geographically--

00:18:46.325 --> 00:18:47.659 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Yeah.

00:18:47.659 --> 00:18:48.827 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: -- as the world's
second longest barrier reef.

00:18:48.827 --> 00:18:52.364 align:middle line:84%
Beautiful, crystal
clear, emerald waters

00:18:52.364 --> 00:18:54.133 align:middle line:90%
on the inside of the reef.

00:18:54.133 --> 00:18:55.467 align:middle line:90%
Very calm.

00:18:55.467 --> 00:18:57.603 align:middle line:84%
It's the only place in the
world where you can have a dock

00:18:57.603 --> 00:18:59.304 align:middle line:84%
in front of your house
right on the ocean.

00:18:59.304 --> 00:19:00.806 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Had your
vacation there before?

00:19:00.806 --> 00:19:01.340 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Oh yeah.

00:19:01.340 --> 00:19:02.141 align:middle line:90%
Many times.

00:19:02.141 --> 00:19:03.042 align:middle line:90%
It's a great vacation spot.

00:19:03.042 --> 00:19:04.143 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Yeah.

00:19:04.143 --> 00:19:05.110 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Great
snorkeling and diving spot.

00:19:05.110 --> 00:19:06.245 align:middle line:84%
One of the greatest
in the world.

00:19:06.245 --> 00:19:08.714 align:middle line:84%
And then the jungles,
whoa, I've--

00:19:08.714 --> 00:19:10.783 align:middle line:84%
you know, I had a place
in Ecuador and I had been

00:19:10.783 --> 00:19:13.686 align:middle line:84%
down the Amazon, nothing
like the rivers of Belize.

00:19:13.686 --> 00:19:14.820 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Nothing like that?

00:19:14.820 --> 00:19:16.055 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Nothing like
the rivers of Belize.

00:19:16.055 --> 00:19:18.957 align:middle line:84%
You know, the lines with
crocodiles, and the storks,

00:19:18.957 --> 00:19:22.161 align:middle line:84%
and howler monkeys, and spider
monkeys and every manner

00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:26.098 align:middle line:84%
of wildlife, beautiful, and
more importantly, the plants.

00:19:26.098 --> 00:19:29.568 align:middle line:90%
There are 2,700 species

00:19:29.568 --> 00:19:31.937 align:middle line:84%
of plants along the
jungle rivers in Belize.

00:19:31.937 --> 00:19:33.272 align:middle line:84%
Meaning, they're
easy to collect.

00:19:33.272 --> 00:19:34.506 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Yes.

00:19:34.506 --> 00:19:36.875 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: And while
companies like Merck and Bayer,

00:19:36.875 --> 00:19:40.279 align:middle line:84%
the large pharmaceuticals
have tested all of them,

00:19:40.279 --> 00:19:42.314 align:middle line:84%
they've only tested them
against specific things

00:19:42.314 --> 00:19:44.783 align:middle line:90%
like does it kill bacteria?

00:19:44.783 --> 00:19:45.617 align:middle line:90%
Yes or no.

00:19:45.617 --> 00:19:46.919 align:middle line:90%
If it doesn't, throw it away.

00:19:46.919 --> 00:19:50.355 align:middle line:84%
I retested these things,
not just to kill bacteria

00:19:50.355 --> 00:19:52.558 align:middle line:84%
but does it interrupt
the communication,

00:19:52.558 --> 00:19:53.792 align:middle line:90%
think back to your-- ?

00:19:53.792 --> 00:19:54.593 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Possible, another
company at that time?

00:19:54.593 --> 00:19:55.794 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Pardon?

00:19:55.794 --> 00:19:56.795 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Another company
you're going to form.

00:19:56.795 --> 00:19:57.763 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: It was
Cormix [phonetic].

00:19:57.763 --> 00:19:58.330 align:middle line:84%
I founded a company
called Cormix.

00:19:58.330 --> 00:19:59.698 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: OK.

00:19:59.698 --> 00:20:02.000 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: -- and I hired some
PhD, a chemist and biologist

00:20:02.000 --> 00:20:04.336 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of local
people to collect plants

00:20:04.336 --> 00:20:05.771 align:middle line:90%
and grind them and extract.

00:20:05.771 --> 00:20:08.173 align:middle line:84%
And I was having
a great old time

00:20:08.173 --> 00:20:11.343 align:middle line:84%
until the army came
in and shut me down.

00:20:11.343 --> 00:20:12.311 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Yeah.

00:20:12.311 --> 00:20:13.745 align:middle line:84%
They came in and
tried to extort you.

00:20:13.745 --> 00:20:14.880 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Well,
the army didn't.

00:20:14.880 --> 00:20:16.949 align:middle line:84%
There was a politician
who tried to extort me.

00:20:16.949 --> 00:20:18.317 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: OK.

00:20:18.317 --> 00:20:20.085 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: I said no and well,
the politicians own the army

00:20:20.085 --> 00:20:22.988 align:middle line:84%
so they sent 42 soldiers
and riot here.

00:20:22.988 --> 00:20:27.092 align:middle line:84%
Shot my dog in front of my
eyes, destroyed my laboratory,

00:20:27.092 --> 00:20:29.328 align:middle line:84%
kept me handcuffed in
the sun for 14 hours

00:20:29.328 --> 00:20:30.562 align:middle line:90%
with my hands behind my back.

00:20:30.562 --> 00:20:31.597 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Were you scared?

00:20:31.597 --> 00:20:32.965 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: No I was
pissed off George.

00:20:32.965 --> 00:20:34.166 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: I don't blame you.

00:20:34.166 --> 00:20:35.901 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: I wasn't
scared at all, I was angry.

00:20:35.901 --> 00:20:37.236 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: I don't blame you.

00:20:37.236 --> 00:20:38.303 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: And then they left.

00:20:38.303 --> 00:20:40.172 align:middle line:84%
The politician came
back a week later

00:20:40.172 --> 00:20:42.141 align:middle line:84%
after I got everything
cleaned up and said, "Gosh,

00:20:42.141 --> 00:20:44.409 align:middle line:84%
I was so sorry to hear
about what happened to you."

00:20:44.409 --> 00:20:45.878 align:middle line:84%
He said, "What a
mistake that was."

00:20:45.878 --> 00:20:47.312 align:middle line:84%
He said, you know, "They
must have been looking

00:20:47.312 --> 00:20:48.647 align:middle line:90%
for somebody else.

00:20:48.647 --> 00:20:50.816 align:middle line:84%
And he, by the way, have you
reconsidered your donation?"

00:20:50.816 --> 00:20:52.217 align:middle line:90%
I said, "Absolutely not."

00:20:52.217 --> 00:20:53.552 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Donation they call it?

00:20:53.552 --> 00:20:54.186 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Right.

00:20:54.186 --> 00:20:55.154 align:middle line:90%
Well, a donation.

00:20:55.154 --> 00:20:56.555 align:middle line:84%
They didn't say give
me the money.

00:20:56.555 --> 00:20:58.223 align:middle line:84%
So why don't you donate to my
campaign and when I get elected,

00:20:58.223 --> 00:21:01.326 align:middle line:84%
I'll give you all of these
lands and tax breaks and--

00:21:01.326 --> 00:21:03.095 align:middle line:90%
I'm not interested, thank you.

00:21:03.095 --> 00:21:04.830 align:middle line:84%
So instead of giving
him the money,

00:21:04.830 --> 00:21:06.064 align:middle line:84%
I called the international
press,

00:21:06.064 --> 00:21:07.366 align:middle line:84%
I called the Wall
Street journal first.

00:21:07.366 --> 00:21:09.234 align:middle line:84%
I said, "You know,
I haven't talked

00:21:09.234 --> 00:21:10.402 align:middle line:90%
to you guys in five years.

00:21:10.402 --> 00:21:11.403 align:middle line:90%
I have a story for you."

00:21:11.403 --> 00:21:12.104 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: And they
knew who you were.

00:21:12.104 --> 00:21:12.804 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Of course.

00:21:12.804 --> 00:21:14.139 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: They remember.

00:21:14.139 --> 00:21:15.407 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: They remember in
New York Times and so I went

00:21:15.407 --> 00:21:18.343 align:middle line:84%
to everybody at the London
Times, people who reported

00:21:18.343 --> 00:21:21.680 align:middle line:84%
on me many times before
and I told my story.

00:21:21.680 --> 00:21:23.815 align:middle line:84%
And it was all over the world
that, you know, McAfee--

00:21:23.815 --> 00:21:24.816 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Now you're
in Belize, right?

00:21:24.816 --> 00:21:26.218 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Yes I was in Belize.

00:21:26.218 --> 00:21:29.354 align:middle line:84%
So I figured, you know, I was
under the mistaken impression

00:21:29.354 --> 00:21:30.322 align:middle line:90%
that all countries have laws.

00:21:30.322 --> 00:21:31.356 align:middle line:90%
[ Laughter ]

00:21:31.356 --> 00:21:34.793 align:middle line:84%
And that these laws
will protect you.

00:21:34.793 --> 00:21:36.795 align:middle line:84%
Well, you know, what
an idiot I am.

00:21:36.795 --> 00:21:39.298 align:middle line:84%
There are no laws in
places like Belize.

00:21:39.298 --> 00:21:41.366 align:middle line:90%
The law is the law of power.

00:21:41.366 --> 00:21:42.634 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Exactly.

00:21:42.634 --> 00:21:44.536 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: You know, the
method of the law is extortion.

00:21:44.536 --> 00:21:50.475 align:middle line:84%
The fundamental drive of the
law is fear and that's it.

00:21:50.475 --> 00:21:53.145 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Your neighbor gets
killed, you and I theorized,

00:21:53.145 --> 00:21:55.113 align:middle line:90%
they bumped him off to get you.

00:21:55.113 --> 00:21:56.582 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: I think they did.

00:21:56.582 --> 00:21:59.551 align:middle line:84%
And this was seven months
later and every single day,

00:21:59.551 --> 00:22:00.953 align:middle line:90%
I got kicked in another story.

00:22:00.953 --> 00:22:03.255 align:middle line:84%
And if you look at that
period, there were thousands

00:22:03.255 --> 00:22:05.224 align:middle line:90%
of newspaper and TV stories

00:22:05.224 --> 00:22:08.126 align:middle line:84%
about McAfee raided,
dog killed--

00:22:08.126 --> 00:22:09.127 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: I was reading
these accounts.

00:22:09.127 --> 00:22:10.729 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Laboratory destroyed.

00:22:10.729 --> 00:22:12.030 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: This poor guy.

00:22:12.030 --> 00:22:14.566 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: But as long as
the press was looking at me,

00:22:14.566 --> 00:22:16.168 align:middle line:84%
the police just couldn't
do anything.

00:22:16.168 --> 00:22:19.037 align:middle line:84%
They couldn't just shoot me in
broad daylight or hire someone

00:22:19.037 --> 00:22:20.973 align:middle line:84%
because it was being
too obvious, right?

00:22:20.973 --> 00:22:23.642 align:middle line:84%
But my neighbor gets whacked
while we want to question him

00:22:23.642 --> 00:22:25.844 align:middle line:84%
like we question all
of the neighbors.

00:22:25.844 --> 00:22:27.946 align:middle line:84%
They didn't say, "We
think you did it,

00:22:27.946 --> 00:22:29.314 align:middle line:84%
we want to question
all the neighbors."

00:22:29.314 --> 00:22:32.017 align:middle line:84%
But Mr. McAfee refuses
to be questioned.

00:22:32.017 --> 00:22:34.653 align:middle line:84%
Duh, and police, if
they question you,

00:22:34.653 --> 00:22:35.654 align:middle line:90%
they can hold you forever.

00:22:35.654 --> 00:22:37.055 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: They hold you forever.

00:22:37.055 --> 00:22:38.690 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: 60 days at the time,
if they don't like your answer,

00:22:38.690 --> 00:22:41.627 align:middle line:84%
set another 60 days
without a court order.

00:22:41.627 --> 00:22:42.894 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: At what
point did you say,

00:22:42.894 --> 00:22:44.763 align:middle line:84%
"I got to get out
or dodge here?"

00:22:44.763 --> 00:22:47.232 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Well, and clear that
it could not-- I kept thinking,

00:22:47.232 --> 00:22:49.434 align:middle line:90%
OK, I can recover this.

00:22:49.434 --> 00:22:52.104 align:middle line:84%
I can-- eventually, the
world is going to see

00:22:52.104 --> 00:22:55.007 align:middle line:84%
that this was a setup
but no, absolutely not.

00:22:55.007 --> 00:22:56.141 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: How did you get out?

00:22:56.141 --> 00:22:56.842 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: It just kept
getting worse and worse.

00:22:56.842 --> 00:22:58.844 align:middle line:90%
That was difficult.

00:22:58.844 --> 00:23:03.415 align:middle line:84%
I had been in Belize long
enough to know how the army

00:23:03.415 --> 00:23:06.918 align:middle line:84%
and the police work and I knew
that number one, they never work

00:23:06.918 --> 00:23:08.954 align:middle line:84%
on rainy days, they don't care
what happens that day, OK?

00:23:08.954 --> 00:23:10.355 align:middle line:90%
So if there's a checkpoint--

00:23:10.355 --> 00:23:13.258 align:middle line:84%
and by the way, they had
checkpoints at all the exits.

00:23:13.258 --> 00:23:14.259 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Looking for you.

00:23:14.259 --> 00:23:16.194 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Looking for me.

00:23:16.194 --> 00:23:18.930 align:middle line:84%
So I knew that-- sort
of it was a rainy day,

00:23:18.930 --> 00:23:20.999 align:middle line:84%
there was this waiver,
everybody through.

00:23:20.999 --> 00:23:24.670 align:middle line:84%
Secondly, I've arranged to have
two reporters from Vice come

00:23:24.670 --> 00:23:26.171 align:middle line:90%
down and exit with me.

00:23:26.171 --> 00:23:29.675 align:middle line:84%
So they got to report it and
I got to have two Americans

00:23:29.675 --> 00:23:31.276 align:middle line:84%
to make it look like
we were a crowd.

00:23:31.276 --> 00:23:32.678 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Yeah.

00:23:32.678 --> 00:23:34.680 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Then I took off one
of my ex-girlfriend's boyfriend

00:23:34.680 --> 00:23:37.949 align:middle line:84%
who was American took him
and myself and my girlfriend

00:23:37.949 --> 00:23:41.386 align:middle line:84%
and I was in disguised and every
checkpoint, they just wave us

00:23:41.386 --> 00:23:43.689 align:middle line:84%
on through from inside
their cars.

00:23:43.689 --> 00:23:45.991 align:middle line:90%
OK, so that was number one.

00:23:45.991 --> 00:23:51.163 align:middle line:84%
Number two, all the borders
including the water passages

00:23:51.163 --> 00:23:53.398 align:middle line:84%
were controlled by
the coast guard.

00:23:53.398 --> 00:23:56.802 align:middle line:84%
So I arranged to have a friend
of mine who look like me

00:23:56.802 --> 00:24:00.572 align:middle line:84%
and pretended to be me be
arrested in Southern Mexico

00:24:00.572 --> 00:24:02.374 align:middle line:84%
and have that spread
over the news.

00:24:02.374 --> 00:24:03.442 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:24:03.442 --> 00:24:04.776 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: So they
thought they had you?

00:24:04.776 --> 00:24:07.079 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: They sent everybody
up north and so I escaped

00:24:07.079 --> 00:24:08.413 align:middle line:90%
over the Southern Border

00:24:08.413 --> 00:24:10.582 align:middle line:84%
and everything was
empty, no one was there.

00:24:10.582 --> 00:24:11.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Gosh.

00:24:11.650 --> 00:24:12.851 align:middle line:84%
And here-- did you
feel secure here now?

00:24:12.851 --> 00:24:14.286 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: No, of course
I don't feel secure here.

00:24:14.286 --> 00:24:15.287 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: You don't?

00:24:15.287 --> 00:24:17.022 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: The police
has a long arm

00:24:17.022 --> 00:24:18.857 align:middle line:84%
and I continue to
talk about them.

00:24:18.857 --> 00:24:20.325 align:middle line:84%
If you'll look at
my blog, I have--

00:24:20.325 --> 00:24:23.261 align:middle line:84%
there's something every other
day that I post, it's true.

00:24:23.261 --> 00:24:27.299 align:middle line:84%
I mean, for example,
there is a--

00:24:27.299 --> 00:24:31.303 align:middle line:84%
OK, I reported when I first came
back the police were selling

00:24:31.303 --> 00:24:35.507 align:middle line:84%
passports to Iranians and
to other terrorist groups.

00:24:35.507 --> 00:24:36.641 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: To get in here or in--

00:24:36.641 --> 00:24:37.909 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: To get into
America, not to get me

00:24:37.909 --> 00:24:39.010 align:middle line:90%
but just to get in to America.

00:24:39.010 --> 00:24:39.678 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Right, right.

00:24:39.678 --> 00:24:40.512 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:24:40.512 --> 00:24:41.480 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Nobody believe me.

00:24:41.480 --> 00:24:43.048 align:middle line:90%
Last week, they reported

00:24:43.048 --> 00:24:48.820 align:middle line:84%
in a Belizean newspaper
someone took 155 files

00:24:48.820 --> 00:24:52.691 align:middle line:84%
from the government and gave
it to the press of people

00:24:52.691 --> 00:24:56.361 align:middle line:84%
that they were buying passports
for 100,000 dollars a pop--

00:24:56.361 --> 00:24:57.596 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: God.

00:24:57.596 --> 00:24:59.031 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: -- from this
one man in the government--

00:24:59.031 --> 00:25:01.199 align:middle line:84%
the man that I had
named previously.

00:25:01.199 --> 00:25:03.869 align:middle line:84%
So I'm not making this stuff
up and it did come to light.

00:25:03.869 --> 00:25:05.337 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Was this the guy
who was trying to shake you

00:25:05.337 --> 00:25:06.705 align:middle line:90%
down or somebody else?

00:25:06.705 --> 00:25:07.372 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: No.

00:25:07.372 --> 00:25:08.740 align:middle line:90%
It was someone else.

00:25:08.740 --> 00:25:10.142 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: OK.

00:25:10.142 --> 00:25:12.210 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: But it's shocking and
what's more shocking George is

00:25:12.210 --> 00:25:13.879 align:middle line:84%
that the news never
gets here to America.

00:25:13.879 --> 00:25:14.579 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: No.

00:25:14.579 --> 00:25:15.714 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: For example,

00:25:15.714 --> 00:25:18.884 align:middle line:84%
one of our most prominent
American citizens,

00:25:18.884 --> 00:25:23.622 align:middle line:84%
he owns for example, the largest
Kentucky Fried Chicken franchise

00:25:23.622 --> 00:25:28.393 align:middle line:84%
in America, he owns oil-leases
in Belize and Pakistan.

00:25:28.393 --> 00:25:30.495 align:middle line:84%
He owns a food processing
company,

00:25:30.495 --> 00:25:34.099 align:middle line:84%
he owns the largest shrimp
farm in Central America,

00:25:34.099 --> 00:25:35.300 align:middle line:90%
a very well connected man.

00:25:35.300 --> 00:25:36.835 align:middle line:90%
He's a commercial pilot.

00:25:36.835 --> 00:25:41.072 align:middle line:84%
Extremely rich, he was one of
the people in this package.

00:25:41.072 --> 00:25:44.376 align:middle line:84%
There's this-- has his passport
photo in all the documentation

00:25:44.376 --> 00:25:45.544 align:middle line:90%
and how much money he paid.

00:25:45.544 --> 00:25:46.611 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Unbelievable.

00:25:46.611 --> 00:25:47.412 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Now you
have to ask yourself,

00:25:47.412 --> 00:25:48.280 align:middle line:90%
why is an American citizen--

00:25:48.280 --> 00:25:49.481 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: What does he need?

00:25:49.481 --> 00:25:51.817 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: He is also of
Muslim descent by the way

00:25:51.817 --> 00:25:55.220 align:middle line:84%
and he owns banks here in
America that are affiliated

00:25:55.220 --> 00:25:57.989 align:middle line:84%
with Muslim terrorists
and with--

00:25:57.989 --> 00:26:01.059 align:middle line:84%
America is just not going to
let him fly around at will

00:26:01.059 --> 00:26:03.562 align:middle line:84%
but with the Belizean passport,
he goes to Belize, he flies,

00:26:03.562 --> 00:26:04.396 align:middle line:90%
you know, where he want.

00:26:04.396 --> 00:26:05.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: This is a huge story.

00:26:05.630 --> 00:26:06.731 align:middle line:90%
Huge.

00:26:06.731 --> 00:26:07.566 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Well, it's
out there for any--

00:26:07.566 --> 00:26:08.934 align:middle line:90%
you could Google it yourself.

00:26:08.934 --> 00:26:11.470 align:middle line:84%
The problem is it doesn't get
reported here in the states.

00:26:11.470 --> 00:26:12.838 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: And these people

00:26:12.838 --> 00:26:15.240 align:middle line:84%
who bought the passports God
knows what they need them for.

00:26:15.240 --> 00:26:16.708 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: I know what
they needed it for.

00:26:16.708 --> 00:26:18.143 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Nice way to
enter the country, right?

00:26:18.143 --> 00:26:19.811 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: A nice way to enter
the country because what happens

00:26:19.811 --> 00:26:22.414 align:middle line:84%
with Belizean passport, you
can travel throughout all

00:26:22.414 --> 00:26:25.083 align:middle line:84%
of Central America and all the
caricom countries that is all

00:26:25.083 --> 00:26:28.587 align:middle line:84%
of the Caribbean-- is
it Caribbean Union.

00:26:28.587 --> 00:26:31.156 align:middle line:84%
In Mexico, you just walk
across like anybody else.

00:26:31.156 --> 00:26:33.825 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: I would hope homeland
security has read this story

00:26:33.825 --> 00:26:35.193 align:middle line:90%
and they're jumping--

00:26:35.193 --> 00:26:36.261 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: If they have, they're
not doing anything about it.

00:26:36.261 --> 00:26:38.396 align:middle line:84%
This man is still free
and flying around.

00:26:38.396 --> 00:26:39.598 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Unbelievable.

00:26:39.598 --> 00:26:43.368 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: So in any case,
it's been an interest--

00:26:43.368 --> 00:26:44.536 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: What a ride John.

00:26:44.536 --> 00:26:45.437 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: It has
been a ride sir.

00:26:45.437 --> 00:26:46.138 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: What a ride.

00:26:46.138 --> 00:26:46.938 align:middle line:90%
What are you doing next?

00:26:46.938 --> 00:26:48.073 align:middle line:90%
What's up--

00:26:48.073 --> 00:26:50.775 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Well, there
are a couple of things.

00:26:50.775 --> 00:26:54.646 align:middle line:84%
When I formed the
company to create privacy

00:26:54.646 --> 00:26:56.648 align:middle line:84%
for its citizenry
electronically,

00:26:56.648 --> 00:26:59.851 align:middle line:84%
it's sort of a secondary
internet.

00:26:59.851 --> 00:27:02.654 align:middle line:84%
It's not to replace the internet
but to give you a switch.

00:27:02.654 --> 00:27:07.192 align:middle line:84%
I mean for example, if you're
Googling, you know, where to eat

00:27:07.192 --> 00:27:09.227 align:middle line:84%
or general information,
you don't care

00:27:09.227 --> 00:27:10.962 align:middle line:84%
if anybody is watching
you usually.

00:27:10.962 --> 00:27:12.364 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: You don't think--

00:27:12.364 --> 00:27:14.165 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: If you're sending a
private message to your wife,

00:27:14.165 --> 00:27:16.067 align:middle line:90%
your girlfriend, your son,

00:27:16.067 --> 00:27:18.503 align:middle line:84%
if you have a private
communication, it doesn't have

00:27:18.503 --> 00:27:20.305 align:middle line:84%
to be a juicy communication
but just something

00:27:20.305 --> 00:27:22.240 align:middle line:84%
that really doesn't
need to be shared,

00:27:22.240 --> 00:27:23.475 align:middle line:84%
then you switch to
private network.

00:27:23.475 --> 00:27:24.943 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: And you switch
over to that, that's smart.

00:27:24.943 --> 00:27:28.413 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: So hopefully, it will
be available in about every year

00:27:28.413 --> 00:27:34.085 align:middle line:84%
and if the NSA lets me build it,
then I think it will be a boon

00:27:34.085 --> 00:27:35.253 align:middle line:90%
for the American citizen.

00:27:35.253 --> 00:27:36.888 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Could they
put the kibosh on it?

00:27:36.888 --> 00:27:38.089 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Well of course.

00:27:38.089 --> 00:27:39.090 align:middle line:84%
It's the government, they
can do what they want.

00:27:39.090 --> 00:27:40.525 align:middle line:84%
They can audit me
a million times--

00:27:40.525 --> 00:27:41.459 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Yeah.

00:27:41.459 --> 00:27:42.727 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: -- they
can, you know,

00:27:42.727 --> 00:27:45.430 align:middle line:84%
they can pass a law saying
this is illegal, whatever.

00:27:45.430 --> 00:27:47.232 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Are you back to stay?

00:27:47.232 --> 00:27:47.999 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: I think so.

00:27:47.999 --> 00:27:49.167 align:middle line:90%
I think so.

00:27:49.167 --> 00:27:52.470 align:middle line:84%
You know, I think I would
be better off trying

00:27:52.470 --> 00:27:56.741 align:middle line:84%
to fix the small ills within
this country than to flee

00:27:56.741 --> 00:27:58.743 align:middle line:84%
from them in two
things which, you know,

00:27:58.743 --> 00:28:00.745 align:middle line:84%
just out of the frying
pan, into the fire maybe.

00:28:00.745 --> 00:28:01.947 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Sure.

00:28:01.947 --> 00:28:03.415 align:middle line:84%
Well, and you got your
taste on the outside.

00:28:03.415 --> 00:28:04.349 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Yes.

00:28:04.349 --> 00:28:05.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: You see
what it's like.

00:28:05.650 --> 00:28:07.519 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: Yes, I have seen
what it's like firsthand.

00:28:07.519 --> 00:28:09.654 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: I've got my
issues with government

00:28:09.654 --> 00:28:12.791 align:middle line:84%
but there's never been
a country like this.

00:28:12.791 --> 00:28:16.361 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: No, there hasn't, you
know, and I will say for anybody

00:28:16.361 --> 00:28:20.432 align:middle line:84%
to hear that we live in the
greatest country on this planet.

00:28:20.432 --> 00:28:21.633 align:middle line:90%
It is not perfect.

00:28:21.633 --> 00:28:22.767 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: People want to--
they want to track you,

00:28:22.767 --> 00:28:24.703 align:middle line:84%
they want to read your
blogs, where do they go?

00:28:24.703 --> 00:28:25.537 align:middle line:90%
How do we do this?

00:28:25.537 --> 00:28:27.238 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Who is mcafee.com?

00:28:27.238 --> 00:28:29.074 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: OK, simple as that.

00:28:29.074 --> 00:28:30.408 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: That's it.

00:28:30.408 --> 00:28:33.778 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: John, as you look
at the future of technology,

00:28:33.778 --> 00:28:36.481 align:middle line:84%
where are we going to
be five years from now?

00:28:36.481 --> 00:28:37.949 align:middle line:90%
I mean, people are saying

00:28:37.949 --> 00:28:40.819 align:middle line:84%
that your desktop
computer will be passe--

00:28:40.819 --> 00:28:41.586 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Of course.

00:28:41.586 --> 00:28:42.354 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Do you think so?

00:28:42.354 --> 00:28:43.188 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: Oh absolutely.

00:28:43.188 --> 00:28:45.390 align:middle line:90%
I mean, already, I am annoyed

00:28:45.390 --> 00:28:49.327 align:middle line:84%
that they are purposely
not putting functions

00:28:49.327 --> 00:28:51.129 align:middle line:90%
in our smartphones like--

00:28:51.129 --> 00:28:52.464 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: That they could.

00:28:52.464 --> 00:28:54.432 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: That they could
like file transfers and things

00:28:54.432 --> 00:28:57.235 align:middle line:84%
so that we still have to buy
laptops and desktops, right?

00:28:57.235 --> 00:28:58.637 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: Smart move,
you're right.

00:28:58.637 --> 00:29:01.606 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: So it boils down to
two things and two things only.

00:29:01.606 --> 00:29:06.011 align:middle line:84%
The size of the screen and your
method of inputting the keypad.

00:29:06.011 --> 00:29:07.078 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: That's right.

00:29:07.078 --> 00:29:08.446 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: But the
keypad is becoming pass,

00:29:08.446 --> 00:29:11.349 align:middle line:84%
you've got an android font for
phone, a current software--

00:29:11.349 --> 00:29:12.651 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Touchscreen.

00:29:12.651 --> 00:29:16.087 align:middle line:84%
>> McAfee: OK so now, have
you used the voice function?

00:29:16.087 --> 00:29:16.955 align:middle line:90%
>> Noory: Yes.

00:29:16.955 --> 00:29:17.922 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: It's spectacular.

00:29:17.922 --> 00:29:19.224 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: I've sent
text via voice.

00:29:19.224 --> 00:29:20.358 align:middle line:90%
>> McAfee: It's spectacular.

00:29:20.358 --> 00:29:22.027 align:middle line:84%
>> Noory: If I want to
do Google, it's voice.

00:29:22.027 --> 00:29:23.228 align:middle line:90%
